properties.Title: Update: High Water Advisory Alert For Portions Of The Red River
properties.Summary:
Description: Update: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure's Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for the Red River from St. Jean Baptiste through the City of Winnipeg (except for Ste. Agathe) due to expected high flows. If you are in the affected area, be watchful of local waterways as flooding is likely to occur. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by the local authorities. Listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Up-to-date information is available at www.gov.mb.ca/flooding and www.manitoba511.ca or stay tuned to local media.
Expires: 2019-11-09T15:00:00-06:00

Area: The Red River from St. Jean Baptiste through the City of Winnipeg except for Ste. Agathe

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. An intensifying low pressure system will track northward into Davis Strait over the next few days. This system will generate strong northwesterly winds gusting to 70-80 km/h late in the day on Saturday and persisting through Sunday. These strong winds combined with 5 to 15 cm of snow will produce blizzard conditions beginning early Saturday evening and lasting through the day on Sunday. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 10 to 15 cm is expected. An intensifying low pressure system will track northward into Davis Strait over the next few days.
